<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Environment, Food and Rural Affairs Select Committee -</title></head><body><div><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence from the Local Government Association [PUB0015]</span></p></div><br style="clear:both; mso-break-type:section-break; page-break-before:auto" /><div><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.11pt; orphans:0; padding-left:9.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">About the LGA</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Local Government </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Association (LGA) is the national voice of local government.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We work with councils to support, promote and improve local government.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We are a politically-led, cross party organisation which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">works on behalf of councils to ensure local government has a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">strong, credible voice with national government.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We aim to influence and set the political agenda on the issues that matter to councils so they are able to deliver local solutions to national problems.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 44.25pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.11pt; orphans:0; padding-left:9.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he LGA is advocating a radical new approach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which provides solutions to how we can deliver public services within an ever-tightening fiscal environment. The LGA’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Rewiring Public Services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is an ambitious programme which would allow local authorities, through greater local autonomy, to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">help communit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ies to meet people’s future needs and aspirations and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">help generate economic growth. </span><br /></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Democratically elected councillors must be at the heart of any programme of public service reform. Councillors are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">crucial</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> reinvigorating local governance, ensuring strong democratic accountability, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">leading</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> local government to make a difference, deliver and be trusted.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Central government can learn much from how councils have delivered efficiencies and come together to share services, not just with other councils but with organisations in all areas of public services. However, councils could achieve much more if they were</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> freed from unnecessary bureaucracy and the direction of artificial Whitehall silos. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.11pt; orphans:0; padding-left:9.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent is the Government’s public service reform programme succeeding in a. empowering citizens, b. improving public services and c. ensuring that public service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">s are accountable to the people who use them and to elected officials?</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">People increasingly feel that English democracy is facing a crisis. Disillusionment with politics, frustration over unequal distribution of power in the United Kingdom,</span><a name="_ednref1"></a><a href="#_edn1">[i]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> and low levels</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> of trust in central government</span><a name="_ednref2"></a><a href="#_edn2">[ii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> have led us to a place where the current model of public services is unsustainable. However well-intentioned Government reforms might be, it is </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ultimately </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">local leadership that </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">can best deliver economic growth, transformed </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">public services and a rejuvenated democracy. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.2.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Rewiring Public Services</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">, the</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> LGA</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> has set out an approach to public service transformation that will give local people a clear say in the important matters that face them and their communities, and a local vote that matters once more. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> challenges England faces require a different appro</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ach that reflects the needs of local communities, based on joined-up services, economic </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">growth </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">and a new democratic deal. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.1pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What evidence is there that citizen-centred approaches to public </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">service design, delivery and choice of provider can deliver better</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">outcomes, </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ensuring not only better value for money, but also</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">greater social, economic and environmental value?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Community budgets </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">look at the whole system rather than </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">individual</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">services; they are rooted in evidence; and they demand new models of investmen</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">t to set up and sustain the most effective interventions.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> Independent analysis</span><a name="_ednref3"></a><a href="#_edn3">[iii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> for the LGA of the work of the four community budget pilot areas showed that</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> if their proposals on health and social care, troubled families and work and skills were implemented across the country</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> up to £20 billion could be saved over five years. The four areas expect to see a range of wider benefits. For example Essex is redesig</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ning its vocational skills such that it will create </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">8,000 additiona</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">l apprenticeships by 2020, with </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">training better aligned to current and future vacancies in the area.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.2.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">What is clear is the community budget led public service reform agenda offers a much g</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">reater potential for ensuring better value for money and improved services. It is therefore essential that all Whitehall Departments buy into this approach and make positive moves </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">to devolve budgets and responsibility to the local level to enable local pub</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">lic service providers to bring resources together to deliver more efficient public services with improved outcomes</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.3.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">These findings are supported by an extensive body of evidence from councils, for example through the customer-led transformation programme</span><a name="_ednref4"></a><a href="#_edn4">[iv]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> and innovative procurement by councils following the introduction of the Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.1pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(a) What are the risks and opportunities of opening up public services to </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">alternative forms of ownership, provision and accountability?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(b)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How do we ensure open access to public services under</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">alternative forms of ownership, provision and control?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(c)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the challenges and opportunities in moving power away</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">from Whitehall and into the hands of citizens?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Public services in England face </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">challenges which require a </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">fundamental</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> response at both national and local level. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ervices must be transformed through local leadership by rebuilding democratic participation, rewiring public services, and revitalising the economy. The risks of staying the</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> same far outweigh those of leading a transformation that ensures public services are effective, efficient and locally responsive.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.2.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The role of elected councillors is </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">crucial </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">in ensuring communities can access responsive, effective, and accountable </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">services. Local government could do much more to rewire public services and rebuild democratic participation. A fundamental redesign of the national framework of local democracy would ensure decisions about local arrangements are made by people who are acc</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ountable to local voters. Reinvigorating this democratic relationship will give communities a meaningful say in the delivery of their services, no matter what form those services take.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.05pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(a)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How successful have the Government’s reforms been in opening up </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">public services to grassroots community groups, rather than to large</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">private or third sector organisations?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(b)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How can public service contracts be designed to enable service</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">users to choose from a wider range of providers, including</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">community-based </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">providers, to achieve self-defined outcomes?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(c) </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What impact has the Community Right to Bid, Community Right</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">to Challenge, and Community Right to Build had on local</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">communities?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Local </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">authorities</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> are crucial in delivering the services people value. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">he P</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ublic Services (Social Value) Act 2012 has added impetus to how councils and other commissioners consider their procurement processes to support a wide range of providers d</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">epending on the outcomes requ</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ired by that particular service: 65 per cent of council</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">s have already adapted their processes to take account of the Act. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.2.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ouncils are</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> however</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> frustrated by </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">some </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">national schemes. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">For instance,</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">the Work Programme should help councils and their partners better support those who are hardest to reach. Despite good intentions, the model was designed, commissioned, implemented and delivered in isolation and at speed, preventing councils and local part</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ners from offering expertise on client groups. In most cases, it has had the effect of providers operating in isolation from one another and local partners. Critically, the model has not led to successful outcomes for those </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">it is meant to help. March 2013 </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">figures suggest all Work Programme providers have failed to support Employment Support Allowance (ESA) claimants, averaging 5.3% aga</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">inst contracted levels of 16.5%</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ednref5"></a><a href="#_edn5">[v]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> June 2013 figures have not improved.</span><a name="_ednref6"></a><a href="#_edn6">[vi]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.3.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">If given the freedoms and responsibilities, local </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">government can make public services effective, efficient and locally responsive</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> through place-based public service budgets. Many</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> councils have </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">lead the way in opening up service delivery</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> in relation to personal budgets</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">, for example through</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> ‘catalogues’</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">, g</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">uides</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">targeted </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">websites.</span><a name="_ednref7"></a><a href="#_edn7">[vii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Councils also work with the users and other stakeholders themsel</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ves before setting up contracts.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">or example </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Central Bed</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">fordshire’</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">s </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">work </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">on </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">procuring domiciliary c</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">,</span><a name="_ednref8"></a><a href="#_edn8">[viii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> or the innovative approaches undertaken by the Co-operative Councils </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">N</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">etwork. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.4.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Councils have a successful </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">record </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of working with their communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Community Rights </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">are one part of a whole host of relationships, activities, and strategies at play across local government. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Data from government indicates l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">evels of interest in the Right to Bid appear high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ednref9"></a><a href="#_edn9">[ix]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Many councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are working positively with local community groups </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and parish councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to implement the Right effectively</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, for example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> through Swale Borough Council’s ‘Localism Prospectus’.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Anecdotal evidence of the Rights to Build and Challenge suggests that the uptake of these Rights is much lower</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.5.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he LGA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has argued </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">formal Communi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ty Right to Challenge process being</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> use</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is a sign that local relationships with community groups are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t working as well as they might be. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A better</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> way to go about the provision of services by parishes or community groups is as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> part of a strong set of local relationships and a good commissioning strategy. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">use of legal rights is a last resort to be avoided if at all possible</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">his is because</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">any councils are taking proactive approaches to engage positively with their local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">communities, such ‘Speak Out Sutton’</span><a name="_ednref10"></a><a href="#_edn10">[x]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and Kirklees’ ‘It’s Time to Talk’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ednref11"></a><a href="#_edn11">[xi]</a></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(a)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How well do different tiers of government or different parts of single </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">public sector organisation, at central, local authority or district</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">councils level, work together</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> to deliv</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">er public services?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 23.65pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(b)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What impact does the Whitehall federal </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">department structure</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">have on contracting for public services that fall across</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">departmental or organisational boundaries?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.7pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(c)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How does the Government ensure that public services develop</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">right kind of leadership as they become more open, more</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">subject to scrutiny and more customer-focused?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Councils</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> recognise the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">impetus</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> of reduc</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">funding</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">and increasing demand </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">as being an imperative for working together</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ednref12"></a><a href="#_edn12">[xii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> Ninety-five per cent of councils now share services, resulting in at least £278 million of efficiency savings.</span><a name="_ednref13"></a><a href="#_edn13">[xiii]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> Sharing services is business as usual for councils; they are now building on that expertise to deliver more effective outcomes for local commun</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ities by working across the public, private, and voluntary and community sector.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The LGA and the National Association for Local Councils (NALC) have also produced a publication illustrating how principal and town and parish councils are working together to</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> best meet the needs of their communities.</span><a name="_ednref14"></a><a href="#_edn14">[xiv]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.2.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">There is nevertheless room for improvement in the way central and local government work together.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The current model of local government in the context of a highly centralised national state will not serve for m</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">uch longer. While there are some instances of more joined-up working, for example the Commissioning Academy programme or the Whitehall secondees to the community budgets areas, they are still too few. The LGA is calling for a new framework for public servi</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ces which is able to be both strategic and locally responsive and which is supported by a more grown-up relationship between local and central government.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.3.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Whitehall’s siloed structures and at times conflicting policy objectives can mean councils find it u</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">nnecessarily difficult to improve outcomes for local people. This has been seen, for example, in working </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">to reduce re-offending</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">, where c</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ouncils are regularly frustrated at a lack of engagement from some Government departments, such as the Department of Hea</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">lth, which are failing to recognise t</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">heir key role in reducing crime, for </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">example through its funding of treatment for people with alcohol or drug addictions.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> The LGA is calling for a Crime Reduction Board that would </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">allow central government to replicate n</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ationally the success achieved by councils and their partners, including the police and health services, through </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">innovative multi</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">-agency community budget areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.4.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">It is l</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ocal government</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">, through its democratically elected councillors, that is best placed to lead rewired public services. This is because they are closest to those affected by the decisions they make. A transformed and independent local government can make public services ef</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">fective, efficient, and locally responsive. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.5.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The LGA proposes that alongside a wide-ranging localisation of public services, remaining national functions be brought together into a single England Office. This would not only reduce bureaucracy and red tape</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> but also remove the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">artificial silos that promote duplication, waste, and conflicting policy drivers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.1pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What examples are there of innovative ways to deliver better public </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">services in local government, from other countries or from other</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">public service pro</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">viders?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">8.1.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The LGA </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">suppo</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">rts councils in their ambitions to find innovative ways to deliver public services. Our Future Councils</span><a name="_ednref15"></a><a href="#_edn15">[xv]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> and Creative Councils</span><a name="_ednref16"></a><a href="#_edn16">[xvi]</a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> programmes show how councils are taking the lead in innovative public service delivery in everything from </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">looked after children and adult social care to energy supply and work readiness. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.1pt; padding-left:10.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(a)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How realistic is it that “choice” can be exercised in public service </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">provision or should we be looking instead at greater control by users</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">so they can ensure that public</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> services become more responsive to</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">changing needs?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(b) </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How do we make sure that all citizens are able to influence public services?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Councils</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> play a crucial role in ensuring that services are delivered in a joined up way that is accountable, maximises efficiencies and provides capacity to support individuals in exercising choice. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The LGA’s </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Rewiring Public Services </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">campaign puts choice at the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">heart of our vision for health and social care by proposing “personal wellbeing budgets” to provide choice and control to individuals for the services and support they require to improve their health, wellbeing and independence, enabling people to make cho</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ices that sustain their independence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">recent </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">announcement of £3.8 billion worth of funding to ensure closer integration between health and social is an opportunity to give </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">some of the most vulnerable people in our society </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">control, placing them at the c</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">entre of their own care and support and, in doing so, provid</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> them with a better service and better qualit</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">y of life. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">The LGA is committed to helping councils work with Clinical Commissioning Groups to seize</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> this </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">opportunity to do something radically diff</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">erent</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.1pt; padding-left:4.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What safeguards should be in place to deal with service providers </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">who fail to deliver services, or who deliver services of an insufficient</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">quality?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">10.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Councillors have the democratic legitimacy to ensure that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">service providers who fail to deliver services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are properly held to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">accoun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t. This is because</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> they have a key leadership role in localised decision-making and service delivery</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">10.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Safeguards are </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">also created by improving</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> contract and supply chain management</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">. The</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">N</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ew EU procurement rules will allow </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">councils</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> to take into account relevant skills and experience of consultants and will enable </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">councils</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> to exclude suppliers with a poor track record.</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> Taken together these are significant steps towards robust safeguar</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">ding mechanisms against poor performance. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.1pt; padding-left:4.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(a)How do we ensure that best practice is shared so it can be replicated </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">in the context of greater diversity of provision?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 25.5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(b)</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Are there any types of public services that you think should not</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">be opened up to new </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">models of design, delivery or provision?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">11.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">Commissioners learn best when they are working together on shared challenges. Building in learning support to programmes such as community budgets and Our Place! is important in making sure that best practice is shared within and between sectors. The LGA </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">s </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">a champion of sharing learning from areas taking a community budgeting approach. </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">We </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">support the Commissioning Academy which brings together senior commissioners from across different parts of the public sector to build a shared understanding of good prac</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">tice in commissioning. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">11.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">However, it is not simply a matter of taking good practice from one area and replicating it in another. Each area has its own geographical, demographic and political context</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt"> which will be reflected in its commissioning and market </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt">support approaches. Councils, through their elected councillors, are best placed to understand and respond to that context, and to take the lead in public service provision.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.1pt; padding-left:4.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How well has the system of Payment by Results worked in the </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">delivery of public se</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">rvices and how do we make it work better?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">12.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">No one service delivery mo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">del will fit all circumstances</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ecisions about how local services are commissioned should be a matter for individual local authorities to decide.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Councils also face challenges in committing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">resources required to develop new model</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of service delivery in a time of severe cuts to local government funding.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The LGA is supporting councils to explore innovative ways of funding service delivery, for exampl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e though social investment. We are working with Social Finance to support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">those</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> councils interested in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">developing social impact bonds </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and other Payment by Results</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">based social investments as part of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the Big Lottery Fund’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Commissioning Better Outcomes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.1pt; padding-left:4.1pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What progress has been made in setting up mutuals as an effective</span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">way of delivering public services?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-10.35pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">utuals are a good service model when deployed in the right way and the right place by councils that choose to do so</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Many </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">councils are looking to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">deliver services through mutuals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, case studies of which are available on the LGA’s website</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ednref17"></a><a href="#_edn17">[xvii]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The LGA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">supports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">councils to explore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a range of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new models of service delivery</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in a number of ways, including</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="color:#000080; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">publishing guidance and case studies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hosting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">regional master classes for councillors on mutuals and other new delivery models</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">working with the Mutuals Taskforce to raise awareness of their work with local authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">running an ongoing programme of productivity support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">working with the Cabinet O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ffice on the Commissioning Academy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">close working with DCLG and Locality to support implementation of Community Right to Challenge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">supporting the Local Partnerships spin out development network.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:FrutigerLTStd-Bold; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_edn1"></a><a href="#_ednref1">[i]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> According to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the British Social Attitudes survey 2013, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">he proportion of people in England who think Scotland gets more than its fair share of public spending has doubled since 2000 to 44%.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Data</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> available at </span><a href="http://www.bsa-30.natcen.ac.uk/read-the-report/devolution/introduction.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bsa-30.natcen.ac.uk/read-the-report/devolution/introduction.aspx</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_edn2"></a><a href="#_ednref2">[ii]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Independent national polling for the LGA shows that 79 per cent of people trust councils to make decisions about the future of local services. Just</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> 11 per cent trust central government to do so.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_edn3"></a><a href="#_ednref3">[iii]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">More information on the community budgets analysis is available at: </span><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/c/document_library/get_file?uuid=97e64451-9102-451a-9161-8226afe10e30&amp;groupId=10171"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.local.</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">gov.uk/c/document_library/get_file?uuid=97e64451-9102-451a-9161-8226afe10e30&amp;groupId=10171</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_edn4"></a><a href="#_ednref4">[iv]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">More information on the programme is available at: </span><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/productivity/-/journal_content/56/10180/3510959/ARTICLE"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.local</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">.gov.uk/productivity/-/journal_content/56/10180/3510959/ARTICLE</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_edn5"></a><a href="#_ednref5">[v]</a><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210226/work-programme-stats-summary-june-2013_v2_020713.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration